This paper is about sparse channel estimation in wireless communication systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The paper also discusses the use of adaptive filtering theory, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions compressive sensing theory, which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.IT and cs.SP, followed by cs.LG, cs.MM, and cs.NA.
